ested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspeech-therapy-helped-my-toddler-throw-fewer-fits-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeech-language%20pathology%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20potential%20career%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20perfect%20fit.%20There%20was%20a%20surge%20in%20jobs%20for%20speech-language%20pathologists%20(SLPs)%20in%202001%2C%20when%20I%20began%20college%20and%20enrolled%20in%20the%20course%20that%20introduced%20the%20major.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20writing%2C%20but%20no%20one%20said%20to%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BChoose%20the%20job%20you%20can't%20live%20without.%26quot%3B%20%3Cem%3EThat%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20advice%20I%20never%20got.%20And%20so%2C%20I%20let%20writing%20slip%20away%20into%20the%20dust%20of%20my%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f4af478-74be-4fb0-969c-bcf113dd2397%5C%22%3EI%20had%20to%20parent%20while%20living%20with%20a%20chronic%20illness%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-a-degree-while-working-full-time-job-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearning%20my%20master's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20the%20field%20as%20an%20SLP%20in%20an%20elementary%20school%20for%20a%20few%20years%20until%20my%20son%20was%20born.%20It%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20say%20bye%20to%20an%20over-filled%20caseload%20and%20endless%20paperwork%2C%20but%20I%20did%20eventually%20miss%20feeling%20like%20a%20professional.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20khakis%20and%20a%20blouse%2C%20I%20wore%20pajamas%20or%20leggings%20on%20a%20good%20day.%20I%20was%20Mom%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%94%20and%20a%20woman%20searching%20for%20a%20diagnosis%20that%20I%20eventually%20discovered%20was%20multiple%20sclerosis%20%E2%80%94%20and%20life%20was%20now%20filled%20with%20many%20firsts%2C%20both%20wonderful%20motherly%20firsts%2C%20and%20frightening%20disease-worsening%20firsts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20intended%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20when%20my%20younger%20son%20was%20in%20full-day%20school%2C%20but%20between%20mothering%20and%20living%20with%20a%20chronic%20illness%2C%20my%20inner%20creativity%20won.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263b96041-386c-4448-be74-3250551dff0f%5C%22%3EI%20started%20writing%20again%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20slowly.%20At%20first%2C%20I%20simply%20wanted%20to%20connect%20with%20others%20who%20were%20also%20living%20with%20an%20undiagnosed%20disease.%20When%20I%20finally%20received%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20I%20then%20hoped%20to%20be%20an%20advocate%20for%20those%20who%20remained%20undiagnosed%20as%20well%20as%20the%20MS%20community%2C%20so%20I%20continued%20writing%20with%20these%20goals%20in%20mind.%20But%2C%20later%2C%20as%20my%20publications%20widened%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20branch%20out%20%E2%80%94%20to%20write%20about%20parenting%2C%20politics%20that%20impacted%20my%20family's%20life%2C%20and%20what%20I%20thought%20about%20the%20recent%20episode%20of%20my%20favorite%20TV%20show.%20I%20wanted%20to%20write%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20a%20degree%20in%20journalism%2C%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20homework%20to%20do.%20I%20joined%20writer's%20groups%20on%20social%20media%20and%20read%20about%20how%20to%20send%20editors%20pitches%20that%20get%20noticed.%20Over%20time%2C%20I%20became%20accustomed%20to%20radio%20silence%20and%20rejections%20from%20editors.%20A%20lot%20of%20behind-the-scenes%20research%20eventually%20enabled%20me%20to%20get%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20whim%2C%20I%20emailed%20an%20editor%20at%20a%20publication%20I%20aspired%20to%20see%20my%20name%20in.%20Like%20any%20enthusiastic%20creator%20with%20a%20goal%2C%20I%20sent%20a%20draft%20of%20an%20essay%20I'd%20been%20working%20on.%20It%20was%20rejected.%20All%20in%20the%20same%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%20I%20landed%20my%20first%20essay%20in%20that%20publication.%20Often%2C%20I%20wonder%20how%20I%20found%20success%20in%20an%20industry%20that%